As the race for who picks the People’s Democratic Party’s (PDP) guber ticket for the July 14 election in Ekiti state gets underway, senator representing Ekiti South, Abiodun Olujimi, has stepped down for former Minister of State for Works, Prince Dayo Adeyeye. Olujimi who urged her supporters to cast their votes for Adeyeye, said she gave up her governorship ambition for stability, peace and progress of the party. 